Essential: fourierdlem42.b


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem42.c


|- ( ph -> C e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem42.bc


|- ( ph -> B < C )

Essential: fourierdlem42.t


|- T = ( C - B )

Essential: fourierdlem42.a


|- ( ph -> A C_ ( B [,] C ) )

Essential: fourierdlem42.af


|- ( ph -> A e. Fin )

Essential: fourierdlem42.ba


|- ( ph -> B e. A )

Essential: fourierdlem42.ca


|- ( ph -> C e. A )

Essential: fourierdlem42.d


|- D = ( abs o. - )

Essential: fourierdlem42.i


|- I = ( ( A X. A ) \ _I )

Essential: fourierdlem42.r


|- R = ran ( D |` I )

Essential: fourierdlem42.e


|- E = inf ( R , RR , < )

Essential: fourierdlem42.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem42.y


|- ( ph -> Y e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem42.j


|- J = ( topGen ` ran (,) )

Essential: fourierdlem42.k


|- K = ( J |`t ( X [,] Y ) )

Essential: fourierdlem42.h


|- H = { x e. ( X [,] Y ) | E. k e. ZZ ( x + ( k x. T ) ) e. A }

Essential: fourierdlem42.15


|- ( ps <-> ( ( ph /\ ( a e. RR /\ b e. RR /\ a < b ) ) /\ E. j e. ZZ E. k e. ZZ ( ( a + ( j x. T ) ) e. A /\ ( b + ( k x. T ) ) e. A ) ) )

The set of points in a moved partition are finite. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.) (Revised by AV, 29-Sep-2020.)

Theorem: fourierdlem42

Essential: fourierdlem48.a


|- ( ph -> A e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem48.b


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem48.altb


|- ( ph -> A < B )

Essential: fourierdlem48.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem48.t


|- T = ( B - A )

Essential: fourierdlem48.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem48.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem48.f


|- ( ph -> F : D --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem48.dper


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. D /\ k e. ZZ ) -> ( x + ( k x. T ) ) e. D )

Essential: fourierdlem48.per


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. D /\ k e. ZZ ) -> ( F ` ( x + ( k x. T ) ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fourierdlem48.cn


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( F |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) e. ( ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fourierdlem48.r


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> R e. ( ( F |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` i ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem48.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem48.z


|- Z = ( x e. RR |-> ( ( |_ ` ( ( B - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) )

Essential: fourierdlem48.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( Z ` x ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem48.ch


|- ( ch <-> ( ( ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) /\ y e. ( ( Q ` i ) [,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) /\ k e. ZZ ) /\ y = ( X + ( k x. T ) ) ) )

The given periodic function F has a right limit at every point in the reals. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem48


|- ( ph -> ( ( F |` ( X (,) +oo ) ) limCC X ) =/= (/) )

Essential: fourierdlem49.a


|- ( ph -> A e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem49.b


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem49.altb


|- ( ph -> A < B )

Essential: fourierdlem49.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem49.t


|- T = ( B - A )

Essential: fourierdlem49.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem49.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem49.d


|- ( ph -> D C_ RR )

Essential: fourierdlem49.f


|- ( ph -> F : D --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem49.dper


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. D /\ k e. ZZ ) -> ( x + ( k x. T ) ) e. D )

Essential: fourierdlem49.per


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. D /\ k e. ZZ ) -> ( F ` ( x + ( k x. T ) ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fourierdlem49.cn


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( F |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) e. ( ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fourierdlem49.l


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> L e. ( ( F |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem49.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem49.z


|- Z = ( x e. RR |-> ( ( |_ ` ( ( B - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) )

Essential: fourierdlem49.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( Z ` x ) ) )

The given periodic function F has a left limit at every point in the reals. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem49


|- ( ph -> ( ( F |` ( -oo (,) X ) ) limCC X ) =/= (/) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.xre


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem50.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = ( -u _pi + X ) /\ ( p ` m ) = ( _pi + X ) ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem50.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem50.v


|- ( ph -> V e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.a


|- ( ph -> A e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem50.b


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem50.altb


|- ( ph -> A < B )

Essential: fourierdlem50.ab


|- ( ph -> ( A [,] B ) C_ ( -u _pi [,] _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.q


|- Q = ( i e. ( 0 ... M ) |-> ( ( V ` i ) - X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.t


|- T = ( { A , B } u. ( ran Q i^i ( A (,) B ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.n


|- N = ( ( # ` T ) - 1 )

Essential: fourierdlem50.s


|- S = ( iota f f Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... N ) , T ) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.j


|- ( ph -> J e. ( 0 ..^ N ) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.u


|- U = ( iota_ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ( ( S ` J ) (,) ( S ` ( J + 1 ) ) ) C_ ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem50.ch


|- ( ch <-> ( ( ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) /\ ( ( S ` J ) (,) ( S ` ( J + 1 ) ) ) C_ ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) /\ k e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) /\ ( ( S ` J ) (,) ( S ` ( J + 1 ) ) ) C_ ( ( Q ` k ) (,) ( Q ` ( k + 1 ) ) ) ) )

Continuity of O and its limits with respect to the S partition. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem50


|- ( ph -> ( U e. ( 0 ..^ M ) /\ ( ( S ` J ) (,) ( S ` ( J + 1 ) ) ) C_ ( ( Q ` U ) (,) ( Q ` ( U + 1 ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem51.a


|- ( ph -> A e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem51.b


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem51.alt0


|- ( ph -> A < 0 )

Essential: fourierdlem51.bgt0


|- ( ph -> 0 < B )

Essential: fourierdlem51.t


|- T = ( B - A )

Essential: fourierdlem51.cfi


|- ( ph -> C e. Fin )

Essential: fourierdlem51.css


|- ( ph -> C C_ ( A [,] B ) )

Essential: fourierdlem51.bc


|- ( ph -> B e. C )

Essential: fourierdlem51.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( ( |_ ` ( ( B - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem51.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem51.exc


|- ( ph -> ( E ` X ) e. C )

Essential: fourierdlem51.d


|- D = ( { ( A + X ) , ( B + X ) } u. { y e. ( ( A + X ) [,] ( B + X ) ) | E. k e. ZZ ( y + ( k x. T ) ) e. C } )

Essential: fourierdlem51.f


|- F = ( iota f f Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... ( ( # ` D ) - 1 ) ) , D ) )

Essential: fourierdlem51.h


|- H = { y e. ( ( A + X ) (,] ( B + X ) ) | E. k e. ZZ ( y + ( k x. T ) ) e. C }

X is in the periodic partition, when the considered interval is centered at X . (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem51


|- ( ph -> X e. ran F )

Essential: fourierdlem63.t


|- T = ( B - A )

Essential: fourierdlem63.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem63.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem63.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem63.c


|- ( ph -> C e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem63.d


|- ( ph -> D e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem63.cltd


|- ( ph -> C < D )

Essential: fourierdlem63.o


|- O = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = C /\ ( p ` m ) = D ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem63.h


|- H = ( { C , D } u. { x e. ( C [,] D ) | E. k e. ZZ ( x + ( k x. T ) ) e. ran Q } )

Essential: fourierdlem63.n


|- N = ( ( # ` H ) - 1 )

Essential: fourierdlem63.s


|- S = ( iota f f Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... N ) , H ) )

Essential: fourierdlem63.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( ( |_ ` ( ( B - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem63.k


|- ( ph -> K e. ( 0 ... M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem63.j


|- ( ph -> J e. ( 0 ..^ N ) )

Essential: fourierdlem63.y


|- ( ph -> Y e. ( ( S ` J ) [,) ( S ` ( J + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem63.eyltqk


|- ( ph -> ( E ` Y ) < ( Q ` K ) )

Essential: fourierdlem63.x


|- X = ( ( Q ` K ) - ( ( E ` Y ) - Y ) )

The upper bound of intervals in the moved partition are mapped to points that are not greater than the corresponding upper bounds in the original partition. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem63


|- ( ph -> ( E ` ( S ` ( J + 1 ) ) ) <_ ( Q ` K ) )

Essential: fourierdlem64.t


|- T = ( B - A )

Essential: fourierdlem64.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem64.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem64.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem64.c


|- ( ph -> C e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem64.d


|- ( ph -> D e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem64.cltd


|- ( ph -> C < D )

Essential: fourierdlem64.h


|- H = ( { C , D } u. { y e. ( C [,] D ) | E. k e. ZZ ( y + ( k x. T ) ) e. ran Q } )

Essential: fourierdlem64.n


|- N = ( ( # ` H ) - 1 )

Essential: fourierdlem64.v


|- V = ( iota f f Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... N ) , H ) )

Essential: fourierdlem64.j


|- ( ph -> J e. ( 0 ..^ N ) )

Essential: fourierdlem64.l


|- L = sup ( { k e. ZZ | ( ( Q ` 0 ) + ( k x. T ) ) <_ ( V ` J ) } , RR , < )

Essential: fourierdlem64.i


|- I = sup ( { j e. ( 0 ..^ M ) | ( ( Q ` j ) + ( L x. T ) ) <_ ( V ` J ) } , RR , < )

The partition V is finer than Q , when Q is moved on the same interval where V lies. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem64


|- ( ph -> ( ( I e. ( 0 ..^ M ) /\ L e. ZZ ) /\ E. i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) E. l e. ZZ ( ( V ` J ) (,) ( V ` ( J + 1 ) ) ) C_ ( ( ( Q ` i ) + ( l x. T ) ) (,) ( ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) + ( l x. T ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem65.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem65.t


|- T = ( B - A )

Essential: fourierdlem65.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem65.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem65.c


|- ( ph -> C e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem65.d


|- ( ph -> D e. ( C (,) +oo ) )

Essential: fourierdlem65.o


|- O = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = C /\ ( p ` m ) = D ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem65.n


|- N = ( ( # ` ( { C , D } u. { y e. ( C [,] D ) | E. k e. ZZ ( y + ( k x. ( B - A ) ) ) e. ran Q } ) ) - 1 )

Essential: fourierdlem65.s


|- S = ( iota f f Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... N ) , ( { C , D } u. { y e. ( C [,] D ) | E. k e. ZZ ( y + ( k x. ( B - A ) ) ) e. ran Q } ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem65.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( ( |_ ` ( ( B - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem65.l


|- L = ( y e. ( A (,] B ) |-> if ( y = B , A , y ) )

Essential: fourierdlem65.z


|- Z = ( ( S ` j ) + ( B - ( E ` ( S ` j ) ) ) )

The distance of two adjacent points in the moved partition is preserved in the original partition. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem65


|- ( ( ph /\ j e. ( 0 ..^ N ) ) -> ( ( E ` ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) ) - ( L ` ( E ` ( S ` j ) ) ) ) = ( ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) - ( S ` j ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem74.xre


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem74.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = ( -u _pi + X ) /\ ( p ` m ) = ( _pi + X ) ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem74.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem74.x


|- ( ph -> X e. ran V )

Essential: fourierdlem74.y


|- ( ph -> Y e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem74.w


|- ( ph -> W e. ( ( F |` ( -oo (,) X ) ) limCC X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem74.h


|- H = ( s e. ( -u _pi [,] _pi ) |-> if ( s = 0 , 0 , ( ( ( F ` ( X + s ) ) - if ( 0 < s , Y , W ) ) / s ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem74.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem74.v


|- ( ph -> V e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem74.r


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> R e. ( ( F |` ( ( V ` i ) (,) ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem74.q


|- Q = ( i e. ( 0 ... M ) |-> ( ( V ` i ) - X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem74.o


|- O = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = -u _pi /\ ( p ` m ) = _pi ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem74.g


|- G = ( RR _D F )

Essential: fourierdlem74.gcn


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( G |` ( ( V ` i ) (,) ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) : ( ( V ` i ) (,) ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem74.e


|- ( ph -> E e. ( ( G |` ( -oo (,) X ) ) limCC X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem74.a


|- A = if ( ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) = X , E , ( ( R - if ( ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) < X , W , Y ) ) / ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) )

Given a piecewise smooth function F , the derived function H has a limit at the upper bound of each interval of the partition Q . (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem74


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> A e. ( ( H |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem75.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = ( -u _pi + X ) /\ ( p ` m ) = ( _pi + X ) ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem75.x

Essential: fourierdlem75.h

Essential: fourierdlem75.m

Essential: fourierdlem75.r

Essential: fourierdlem75.o

Essential: fourierdlem75.a


|- A = if ( ( V ` i ) = X , E , ( ( R - if ( ( V ` i ) < X , W , Y ) ) / ( Q ` i ) ) )

Given a piecewise smooth function F , the derived function H has a limit at the lower bound of each interval of the partition Q . (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Essential: fourierdlem79.t


|- T = ( B - A )

Essential: fourierdlem79.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem79.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem79.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem79.c


|- ( ph -> C e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem79.d


|- ( ph -> D e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem79.cltd


|- ( ph -> C < D )

Essential: fourierdlem79.o


|- O = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = C /\ ( p ` m ) = D ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem79.h


|- H = ( { C , D } u. { x e. ( C [,] D ) | E. k e. ZZ ( x + ( k x. T ) ) e. ran Q } )

Essential: fourierdlem79.n


|- N = ( ( # ` H ) - 1 )

Essential: fourierdlem79.s


|- S = ( iota f f Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... N ) , H ) )

Essential: fourierdlem79.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( ( |_ ` ( ( B - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem79.l


|- L = ( y e. ( A (,] B ) |-> if ( y = B , A , y ) )

Essential: fourierdlem79.z


|- Z = ( ( S ` j ) + if ( ( ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) - ( S ` j ) ) < ( ( Q ` 1 ) - A ) , ( ( ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) - ( S ` j ) ) / 2 ) , ( ( ( Q ` 1 ) - A ) / 2 ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem79.i


|- I = ( x e. RR |-> sup ( { i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) | ( Q ` i ) <_ ( L ` ( E ` x ) ) } , RR , < ) )

E projects every interval of the partition induced by S on H into a corresponding interval of the partition induced by Q on [ A , B ] . (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Essential: fourierdlem80.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem80.xre


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem80.a


|- ( ph -> A e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem80.b


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem80.ab


|- ( ph -> ( A [,] B ) C_ ( -u _pi [,] _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.n0


|- ( ph -> -. 0 e. ( A [,] B ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.c


|- ( ph -> C e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem80.o


|- O = ( s e. ( A [,] B ) |-> ( ( ( F ` ( X + s ) ) - C ) / ( 2 x. ( sin ` ( s / 2 ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.i


|- I = ( ( X + ( S ` j ) ) (,) ( X + ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.fbdioo


|- ( ( ph /\ j e. ( 0 ..^ N ) ) -> E. w e. RR A. t e. I ( abs ` ( F ` t ) ) <_ w )

Essential: fourierdlem80.fdvbdioo


|- ( ( ph /\ j e. ( 0 ..^ N ) ) -> E. z e. RR A. t e. I ( abs ` ( ( RR _D ( F |` I ) ) ` t ) ) <_ z )

Essential: fourierdlem80.sf


|- ( ph -> S : ( 0 ... N ) --> ( A [,] B ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.slt


|- ( ( ph /\ j e. ( 0 ..^ N ) ) -> ( S ` j ) < ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.sjss


|- ( ( ph /\ j e. ( 0 ..^ N ) ) -> ( ( S ` j ) [,] ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) ) C_ ( A [,] B ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.relioo


|- ( ( ( ph /\ r e. ( A [,] B ) ) /\ -. r e. ran S ) -> E. k e. ( 0 ..^ N ) r e. ( ( S ` k ) (,) ( S ` ( k + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fdv


|- ( ( ph /\ j e. ( 0 ..^ N ) ) -> ( RR _D ( F |` I ) ) : I --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem80.y


|- Y = ( s e. ( ( S ` j ) (,) ( S ` ( j + 1 ) ) ) |-> ( ( ( F ` ( X + s ) ) - C ) / ( 2 x. ( sin ` ( s / 2 ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem80.ch


|- ( ch <-> ( ( ( ( ( ph /\ j e. ( 0 ..^ N ) ) /\ w e. RR ) /\ z e. RR ) /\ A. t e. I ( abs ` ( F ` t ) ) <_ w ) /\ A. t e. I ( abs ` ( ( RR _D ( F |` I ) ) ` t ) ) <_ z ) )

The derivative of O is bounded on the given interval. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem80


|- ( ph -> E. b e. RR A. s e. dom ( RR _D O ) ( abs ` ( ( RR _D O ) ` s ) ) <_ b )

Essential: fourierdlem81.a


|- ( ph -> A e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem81.b


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem81.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem81.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem81.t


|- ( ph -> T e. RR+ )

Essential: fourierdlem81.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem81.fper


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. ( A [,] B ) ) -> ( F ` ( x + T ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fourierdlem81.s


|- S = ( i e. ( 0 ... M ) |-> ( ( Q ` i ) + T ) )

Essential: fourierdlem81.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> CC )

Essential: fourierdlem81.cncf


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( F |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) e. ( ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fourierdlem81.r


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> R e. ( ( F |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` i ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem81.l


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> L e. ( ( F |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem81.g


|- G = ( x e. ( ( Q ` i ) [,] ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) |-> if ( x = ( Q ` i ) , R , if ( x = ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) , L , ( F ` x ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem81.h


|- H = ( x e. ( ( S ` i ) [,] ( S ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) |-> ( G ` ( x - T ) ) )

The integral of a piecewise continuous periodic function F is unchanged if the domain is shifted by its period T . In this lemma, T is assumed to be strictly positive. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem81


|- ( ph -> S. ( ( A + T ) [,] ( B + T ) ) ( F ` x ) _d x = S. ( A [,] B ) ( F ` x ) _d x )

Essential: fourierdlem84.1


|- ( ph -> A e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem84.2


|- ( ph -> B e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem84.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem84.xre


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem84.p


|- P = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = ( A + X ) /\ ( p ` m ) = ( B + X ) ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem84.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem84.v


|- ( ph -> V e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem84.fcn


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( F |` ( ( V ` i ) (,) ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) e. ( ( ( V ` i ) (,) ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fourierdlem84.r


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> R e. ( ( F |` ( ( V ` i ) (,) ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( V ` i ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem84.l


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> L e. ( ( F |` ( ( V ` i ) (,) ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( V ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem84.q


|- Q = ( i e. ( 0 ... M ) |-> ( ( V ` i ) - X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem84.o


|- O = ( m e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... m ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = A /\ ( p ` m ) = B ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ m ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem84.d


|- ( ph -> D e. ( RR -cn-> RR ) )

Essential: fourierdlem84.g


|- G = ( s e. ( A [,] B ) |-> ( ( F ` ( X + s ) ) x. ( D ` s ) ) )

If F is piecewise coninuous and D is continuous, then G is continuous. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem84


|- ( ph -> G e. L^1 )

Given a piecewise continuous function and changing the interval and the partition, the limit at the upper bound of each interval of the moved partition is still finite. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Essential: fourierdlem94.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem94.t


|- T = ( 2 x. _pi )

Essential: fourierdlem94.per


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. RR ) -> ( F ` ( x + T ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fourierdlem94.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem94.p


|- P = ( n e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... n ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = -u _pi /\ ( p ` n ) = _pi ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ n ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem94.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem94.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem94.dvcn


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) e. ( ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fourierdlem94.dvlb


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` i ) ) =/= (/) )

Essential: fourierdlem94.dvub


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) =/= (/) )

For a piecewise smooth function, the left and the right limits exist at any point. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem94


|- ( ph -> ( ( ( F |` ( -oo (,) X ) ) limCC X ) =/= (/) /\ ( ( F |` ( X (,) +oo ) ) limCC X ) =/= (/) ) )

For a piecewise smooth function, the left and the right limits exist at any point. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

|- ( ch <-> ( ( ( ( ( ph /\ e e. RR+ ) /\ d e. ( -u _pi (,) 0 ) ) /\ k e. NN ) /\ ( abs ` S. ( d (,) 0 ) ( ( U ` s ) x. ( sin ` ( ( k + ( 1 / 2 ) ) x. s ) ) ) _d s ) < ( e / 2 ) ) /\ ( abs ` S. ( -u _pi (,) d ) ( ( U ` s ) x. ( sin ` ( ( k + ( 1 / 2 ) ) x. s ) ) ) _d s ) < ( e / 2 ) ) )

The half lower part of the integral equal to the fourier partial sum, converges to half the left limit of the original function. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

The half upper part of the integral equal to the fourier partial sum, converges to half the right limit of the original function. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

The integral of a piecewise continuous periodic function F is unchanged if the domain is shifted by any positive value X . This lemma generalizes ~ fourierdlem92 where the integral was shifted by the exact period. This lemma uses local definitions, so that the proof is more readable. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

The fourier partial sum for F is the sum of two integrals, with the same integrand involving F and the Dirichlet Kernel D , but on two opposite intervals. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem112.d


|- D = ( m e. NN |-> ( y e. RR |-> if ( ( y mod ( 2 x. _pi ) ) = 0 , ( ( ( 2 x. m ) + 1 ) / ( 2 x. _pi ) ) , ( ( sin ` ( ( m + ( 1 / 2 ) ) x. y ) ) / ( ( 2 x. _pi ) x. ( sin ` ( y / 2 ) ) ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.p


|- P = ( n e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... n ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = -u _pi /\ ( p ` n ) = _pi ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ n ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem112.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem112.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.n


|- N = ( ( # ` ( { ( -u _pi + X ) , ( _pi + X ) } u. { y e. ( ( -u _pi + X ) [,] ( _pi + X ) ) | E. k e. ZZ ( y + ( k x. T ) ) e. ran Q } ) ) - 1 )

Essential: fourierdlem112.v


|- V = ( iota f f Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... N ) , ( { ( -u _pi + X ) , ( _pi + X ) } u. { y e. ( ( -u _pi + X ) [,] ( _pi + X ) ) | E. k e. ZZ ( y + ( k x. T ) ) e. ran Q } ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem112.xran


|- ( ph -> X e. ran V )

Essential: fourierdlem112.t


|- T = ( 2 x. _pi )

Essential: fourierdlem112.fper


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. RR ) -> ( F ` ( x + T ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.fcn

Essential: fourierdlem112.c

Essential: fourierdlem112.u

Essential: fourierdlem112.fdvcn

Essential: fourierdlem112.e

Essential: fourierdlem112.r

Essential: fourierdlem112.a


|- A = ( n e. NN0 |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.b


|- B = ( n e. NN |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.z


|- Z = ( m e. NN |-> ( ( ( A ` 0 ) / 2 ) + sum_ n e. ( 1 ... m ) ( ( ( A ` n ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. X ) ) ) + ( ( B ` n ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. X ) ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.23


|- S = ( n e. NN |-> ( ( ( A ` n ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. X ) ) ) + ( ( B ` n ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. X ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem112.fbd

Essential: fourierdlem112.fdvbd

Essential: fourierdlem112.25

Essential: fourierdlem113.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem113.t


|- T = ( 2 x. _pi )

Essential: fourierdlem113.per


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. RR ) -> ( F ` ( x + T ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fourierdlem113.l


|- ( ph -> L e. ( ( F |` ( -oo (,) X ) ) limCC X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.r


|- ( ph -> R e. ( ( F |` ( X (,) +oo ) ) limCC X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.p


|- P = ( n e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... n ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = -u _pi /\ ( p ` n ) = _pi ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ n ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem113.m


|- ( ph -> M e. NN )

Essential: fourierdlem113.q


|- ( ph -> Q e. ( P ` M ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.dvcn


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) e. ( ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.dvlb


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` i ) ) =/= (/) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.dvub


|- ( ( ph /\ i e. ( 0 ..^ M ) ) -> ( ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( ( Q ` i ) (,) ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) ) limCC ( Q ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) =/= (/) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.a


|- A = ( n e. NN0 |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.b


|- B = ( n e. NN |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.15


|- S = ( n e. NN |-> ( ( ( A ` n ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. X ) ) ) + ( ( B ` n ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. X ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( ( |_ ` ( ( _pi - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem113.exq


|- ( ph -> ( E ` X ) e. ran Q )

Fourier series convergence for periodic, piecewise smooth functions. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem113


|- ( ph -> ( seq 1 ( + , S ) ~~> ( ( ( L + R ) / 2 ) - ( ( A ` 0 ) / 2 ) ) /\ ( ( ( A ` 0 ) / 2 ) + sum_ n e. NN ( ( ( A ` n ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. X ) ) ) + ( ( B ` n ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. X ) ) ) ) ) = ( ( L + R ) / 2 ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fourierdlem114.t


|- T = ( 2 x. _pi )

Essential: fourierdlem114.per


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. RR ) -> ( F ` ( x + T ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.g


|- G = ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.dmdv


|- ( ph -> ( ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) \ dom G ) e. Fin )

Essential: fourierdlem114.gcn


|- ( ph -> G e. ( dom G -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.rlim

Essential: fourierdlem114.llim


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. ( ( -u _pi (,] _pi ) \ dom G ) ) -> ( ( G |` ( -oo (,) x ) ) limCC x ) =/= (/) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.x

Essential: fourierdlem114.l

Essential: fourierdlem114.r


|- ( ph -> R e. ( ( F |` ( X (,) +oo ) ) limCC X ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.a


|- A = ( n e. NN0 |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.b


|- B = ( n e. NN |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.s


|- S = ( n e. NN |-> ( ( ( A ` n ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. X ) ) ) + ( ( B ` n ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. X ) ) ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.p


|- P = ( n e. NN |-> { p e. ( RR ^m ( 0 ... n ) ) | ( ( ( p ` 0 ) = -u _pi /\ ( p ` n ) = _pi ) /\ A. i e. ( 0 ..^ n ) ( p ` i ) < ( p ` ( i + 1 ) ) ) } )

Essential: fourierdlem114.e


|- E = ( x e. RR |-> ( x + ( ( |_ ` ( ( _pi - x ) / T ) ) x. T ) ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.h


|- H = ( { -u _pi , _pi , ( E ` X ) } u. ( ( -u _pi [,] _pi ) \ dom G ) )

Essential: fourierdlem114.m


|- M = ( ( # ` H ) - 1 )

Essential: fourierdlem114.q


|- Q = ( iota g g Isom < , < ( ( 0 ... M ) , H ) )

Fourier series convergence for periodic, piecewise smooth functions. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fourierdlem114


|- ( ph -> ( seq 1 ( + , S ) ~~> ( ( ( L + R ) / 2 ) - ( ( A ` 0 ) / 2 ) ) /\ ( ( ( A ` 0 ) / 2 ) + sum_ n e. NN ( ( ( A ` n ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. X ) ) ) + ( ( B ` n ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. X ) ) ) ) ) = ( ( L + R ) / 2 ) ) )

Fourier serier convergence, for piecewise smooth functions. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Fourier series convergence for periodic, piecewise smooth functions. The series converges to the average value of the left and the right limit of the function. Thus, if the function is continuous at a given point, the series converges exactly to the function value, see ~ fouriercnp . Notice that for a piecewise smooth function, the left and right limits always exist, see ~ fourier2 for an alternative form of the theorem that makes this fact explicit. When the first derivative is continuous, a simpler version of the theorem can be stated, see ~ fouriercn . (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Essential: fouriersw.t


|- T = ( 2 x. _pi )

Essential: fouriersw.f


|- F = ( x e. RR |-> if ( ( x mod T ) < _pi , 1 , -u 1 ) )

Essential: fouriersw.x


|- X e. RR

Essential: fouriersw.z


|- S = ( n e. NN |-> ( ( sin ` ( ( ( 2 x. n ) - 1 ) x. X ) ) / ( ( 2 x. n ) - 1 ) ) )

Essential: fouriersw.y


|- Y = if ( ( X mod _pi ) = 0 , 0 , ( F ` X ) )

Fourier series convergence, for the square wave function. Where F is discontinuous, the series converges to 0 , the average value of the left and the right limits. Notice that F is an odd function and its Fourier expansion has only sine terms (coefficients for cosine terms are zero). (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fouriersw


|- ( ( ( 4 / _pi ) x. sum_ k e. NN ( ( sin ` ( ( ( 2 x. k ) - 1 ) x. X ) ) / ( ( 2 x. k ) - 1 ) ) ) = Y /\ seq 1 ( + , S ) ~~> ( ( _pi / 4 ) x. Y ) )

Disjoint


F n x

Disjoint


G x

Disjoint


T x

Disjoint


X n x

Disjoint


ph x

Essential: fouriercn.f


|- ( ph -> F : RR --> RR )

Essential: fouriercn.t


|- T = ( 2 x. _pi )

Essential: fouriercn.per


|- ( ( ph /\ x e. RR ) -> ( F ` ( x + T ) ) = ( F ` x ) )

Essential: fouriercn.dv


|- ( ph -> ( RR _D F ) e. ( RR -cn-> CC ) )

Essential: fouriercn.g


|- G = ( ( RR _D F ) |` ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) )

Essential: fouriercn.x


|- ( ph -> X e. RR )

Essential: fouriercn.a


|- A = ( n e. NN0 |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

Essential: fouriercn.b


|- B = ( n e. NN |-> ( S. ( -u _pi (,) _pi ) ( ( F ` x ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. x ) ) ) _d x / _pi ) )

If the derivative of F is continuous, then the Fourier series for F converges to F everywhere and the hypothesis are simpler than those for the more general case of a piecewise smooth function ( see ~ fourierd for a comparison). (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)

Theorem: fouriercn


|- ( ph -> ( ( ( A ` 0 ) / 2 ) + sum_ n e. NN ( ( ( A ` n ) x. ( cos ` ( n x. X ) ) ) + ( ( B ` n ) x. ( sin ` ( n x. X ) ) ) ) ) = ( F ` X ) )
